and allocated to the agency for that fiscal year when tobacco
SB153 Enrolled
57 revenues are available for the respective agency. In the event
58 tobacco revenues are not available for the respective agency
59 until later in the fiscal year then the respective agency
60 shall be allocated an equal quarterly allotment for the
61 quarters that funds are available at the beginning of those
62 quarters. Such allocation shall be made and be available for
63 expenditure by the agency within five working days of the
64 commencement of the quarter. If additional sums are
65 appropriated or allocated, or both, during the fiscal year,
66 these sums shall be equally allocated to the respective agency
67 among the remaining quarters of the fiscal year or may be
68 allocated to the respective agency in one sum if revenues are
69 available. The Department of Early Childhood Education shall
70 be notified in writing of all appropriations and allocations
71 from the Children First Trust Fund by the Director of Finance.
72 (4) Allocations from the Children First Trust Fund are
73 conditioned upon the receipt of tobacco revenues.
74 (c) Allocations received pursuant to Section 1 shall be
75 expended in accordance with Section 41-15B-2.2, Code of
76 Alabama 1975.
77 (d) At the conclusion of the fiscal year, any remaining
78 sums in the Children First Trust Fund shall remain in the fund
79 and shall not revert to the State General Fund or to any other
80 fund.
