99 the fiscal year ending September 30, 2027, shall be
100 conditionally appropriated, conditioned upon the
101 recommendation of the Director of Finance, the Chairman of the
102 House Ways and Means General Fund Committee and the Chairman
103 of the Senate Finance and Taxation-General Fund Committee, and
104 approval of the Governor.
105 Section 5. The Executive Budget Office and the Director
106 of Finance shall allot funds appropriated from the Children
107 First Trust Fund only following the certification by the
108 Secretary of the Department of Early Childhood Education that
109 a plan of investment has been approved for each agency. The
110 Secretary of the Department of Early Childhood Education shall
111 prescribe the form and format on which each agency receiving
112 appropriated funds herein shall submit a plan of investment of
Page 4

appropriated funds herein shall submit a plan of investment of
SB153 Enrolled
113 said appropriated funds. The plan of investment shall include,
114 but not be limited to, a minimum of four (4) quality assurance
115 items on which a periodic report, as required by the approved
116 plan of investment, is made and as audited by the Examiners of
117 Public Accounts. Quality assurance items shall include the
118 number of children receiving service, an identifiable measure
119 of success of services provided and a prioritized standard of
120 successful measures for future plans of investment. It is the
121 intent of the Legislature that the Secretary of the Department
122 of Early Childhood Education shall be responsible for
123 providing a standard of measurement by which a clear
124 determination can be made through operational reporting and
125 audit reporting of a measurable success of funds appropriated
126 and invested from the Children First Trust Fund; insure funds
127 appropriated herein are invested in viable programs; insure
128 and promote the leverage of appropriated funds herein in every
129 possible manner and coordinated in all possible ways the
130 investment of funds by each service provider to insure that no
131 unproductive expenditures or duplication occurs. The Secretary
132 of the Department of Early Childhood Education shall notify
133 legislators representing the area where a grant from the
134 Children First Trust Fund is designated. The notification
135 shall occur ten days before the funds reach the recipient
136 agency.
137 Section 6. The Secretary of the Department of Early
138 Childhood Education shall report each approved plan of
139 investment to the Joint Interim Legislative Oversight
140 Committee and the Alabama Children's Policy Council. The
Page 5

Committee and the Alabama Children's Policy Council. The
